<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="230" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[160,1156,262,531]" pageId="3" pageNumber="230">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,282,262,288]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="230">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This genus can be characterised by the following combination of features: Antenna of female filiform, without defined club, with last seven or eight flagellomeres with rhinaria. Mesosoma not much longer than high. Mesoscutum without notauli. Scutellar foveae sculptured at base. Dorsal surface of scutellum coarsely sculptured, can be reticulate-rugose, reticulate-areolate or areolate-rugose, never smooth or striated. Scutellar plate without glandular pit. Wings rounded apically, hairless towards the base of wing. Marginal cell of fore wing can be partially or completely open. Hairy ring at base of syntergum with a very short interruption dorsally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="230" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[160,1156,590,755]" pageId="3" pageNumber="230">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,310,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="230">
<collectingRegion box="[160,305,590,616]" name="Distribution" pageId="3" pageNumber="230">Distribution</collectingRegion>
.
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[326,630,591,616]" pageId="3" pageNumber="230">
<collectingCountry box="[326,451,591,616]" name="Argentina" pageId="3" pageNumber="230">Argentina</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingRegion box="[467,630,591,616]" country="Argentina" name="Ciudad Autonoma de Buenos Aires" pageId="3" pageNumber="230">Buenos Aires</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
. Otamendi (
<bibRefCitation author="Diaz NB &amp; Gallardo FE &amp; Gaddi AL &amp; Cabrera Walsh G" box="[779,968,591,616]" pageId="3" pageNumber="230" pagination="603 - 607" refId="ref4593" refString="Diaz NB, Gallardo FE, Gaddi AL, Cabrera Walsh G. 2009. Description of a new genus and species of Eucoilinae (Hymenoptera: Cynipoidea: Figitidae) parasitoid of ephydridae (Diptera). Ann Entomol Soc Am. 104 (4): 603 - 607." type="journal article" year="2009">Díaz et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
), La Plata (new record) and Ensenada (new record). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[570,675,626,651]" pageId="3" pageNumber="230">
<collectingRegion box="[570,675,626,651]" country="Argentina" name="Misiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="230">Misiones</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
. Yacutinga (new record). According to the biogeographical scheme of 
<bibRefCitation author="Arana MD &amp; Martinez GA &amp; Oggero AJ &amp; Natale ES &amp; Morrone JJ" box="[473,678,660,685]" pageId="3" pageNumber="230" pagination="420 - 422" refId="ref4362" refString="Arana MD, Martinez GA, Oggero AJ, Natale ES, Morrone JJ. 2017. Map and shapefile of the biogeographic provinces of Argentina. Zootaxa. 4341 (3): 420 - 422." type="journal article" year="2017">Arana et al. (2017)</bibRefCitation>
, this distribution range falls within the the Neotropical region, Chacoan subregion, Pampean province for Buenos Aires, and Parana Forest province, for Misiones.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
